sentences: Greg Abate (born May 31, 1947) is a jazz saxophonist, flautist, composer, and arranger.
After working for several years in California, he returned to Berklee in 1972 to finish his education.
After working for several years in California, he returned to Berklee in 1972 to finish his education.
During a second trip to Los Angeles he was hired to play alto saxophone in the Ray Charles band in 1973 and '74.
The group's only album, Without Boundaries, was released in 1980.
In 1986 he was hired by Dick Johnson to play tenor saxophone in the Artie Shaw band.
In April 2016 Abate was among eight inductees for the Rhode Island Music Hall of Fame.
Horace Is Here: A Tribute to Horace Silver (Rhombus, 2011)
The Greg Abate Quintet Featuring Phil Woods (Posi-Tone, 2012)
Kindred Spirits: Live at Chan's (Whaling City Sound, 2016)
